==English==

===Noun phrase===
'''Greek numeral''' (''plural'': '''Greek numerals''')
# One of the '''[[Greek numerals]]'''. A [[symbol]] formed from one or more of the letters of the [[Greek alphabet]] which has been modified by the addition of a mark, thus: <big>Δ'  θ'</big>. These are used to numerate monarchs, chapters, etc as [[Roman numeral]]s are used in English.
# One of the words of the [[Greek]] language used to represent a [[number]].

